$interpreted: Sophie: Rune, what's the matter?
Rune: Joan...is gone.
Sophie: Hasn't she been behind us this whole time?
Ru-yi: We're being followed!!
Hanbei: Who's there? Who dares follow us?
Clark: Umm...everybody, please calm down. I feel we've had a misunderstanding...
Sophie: Now that you say it, she looks familiar...
Sophie: Joan!? What...are you wearing?
Joan: The sixth rule of being a thief: Don't overdo your disguise, this is the way of the wise.
Maria: Maria wants one!
Maria: New~Out~Fit~
Hutchinson: Did Joan learn her thievery skills from her master?
Joan: My master is not a thief, but the god of love. There's no woman in this world he can't have!
Hutchinson: I see...
Ru-yi: Hanbei, she's been duped by a guy, hasn't she...? Shouldn't we let her know what's going on?
Hanbei: Nonsense! If we let the cat out of the bag, she definitely won't help us!
Maria: Recording - - - Joan's master is the god of love.
Clark: Maria, you don't have to record useless information.
Rune: Sophie, what is love?
Sophie: Love is...it's...umm...it's...
Rune: Sophie's face is red...like before.
Sophie: M-M-My face isn't red! It's just too hot...
Sophie: Wow! It's so hot, isn't it...!?
Joan: The world of love is deep and abstruse. After I rescue my master I'll have him teach you!
Rune: I want to learn...
Clark: Why would Yusuf want to capture your master?
Joan: For the Lizards, my master is considered a legendary delicacy. Yusuf employed me to kidnap him so he could be used as a prize at the casino.
Sophie: You kidnapped your own master?
Joan: It was only after I captured him that I discovered he was the god of love. If I don't rescue him then he's going to be eaten.
Sophie: Folks, let's get going!
Sophie: When we get in, everybody remember...
Sophie: ...keep a low profile...
Sophie: What's going on here...why are there so many security officers on duty?
Joan: Hey~ Don't waste your breath, I've already sent a letter notifying them of our entrance.
Sophie: What!? You sent a letter?
Joan: The second rule of being a thief: If you don't let them know you're coming, there can't be a grand entrance.
Clark: *sigh*...it was already going to be hard enough. Now it's going to be nearly impossible.
Bodyguard: Hey! Who goes there!?
Bodyguard: Isn't that the signature move of the "Thief of the Gleaming Star"? Look at that ridiculous outfit. It's got to be her!
Joan: I'm the Th—
Sophie: Shhhhhh—!!!
Bodyguard: Who'd she say she was?
Sophie: This poor child, she has trouble with the "th" sound...*chuckles nervously*...
Bodyguard: Whatever! Grab 'em! We'll figure it out later!
Bodyguard: Rats! Quick, call more men!
Hutchinson: Isn't this for delivering food?
Brunette Rabbit: Helloooooo, it's me~
Clark: Ummm...so...this is quite the casino.
Maria: Master Clark, your eyes seem locked in one place. Is something the matter?
Rune: The rabbits...make me feel happy...
Hutchinson: H-H-H-Here you are...
Brunette Rabbit: Thank you, handsome gentleman~
Brunette Rabbit: *kisses*
Blonde Rabbit: *kisses*
Brunette Rabbit: I'm so sorry! The security guards have been too hard on you fine guests, haven't they?
Brunette Rabbit: How about to make up for it? We'll take you to wherever you need to go~
Sophie: You...umm...we can stay?
Brunette Rabbit: Huh? Of course!!
Blonde Rabbit: The secret to keeping a casino open for a long time is to never kick out customers who still have money to spend!
Blonde Rabbit: The customer is king. Now how could we be so meany weeny to you kings and queens?
Brunette Rabbit: Please, esteemed guests, follow me. Here you are~
Sophie: You, you, you, and you!!
Sophie: You four are so obvious. Stay put!
Clark: Umm...Maria needs someone to keep an eye on her. I'll stay here as well.
Sophie: Sorry, Clark. We need somebody who understands Runes. You've got to help us find the hidden room.
Clark: *sigh*...alright. Let's do this~
